Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

Responses\: success - The user was notified. failure - Notification failed. 379eeed2-0a73-4bb9-b26b-df9c95f37a71.c82b54a6-4c37-4c08-bec5-c6f7dc283f6c.prompt=Proxy Username\: 379eeed2-0a73-4bb9-b26b-df9c95f37a71.cefbb4df-24de-4e0d-9f60-b66bc668ef21.prompt=Username\: 379eeed2-0a73-4bb9-b26b-df9c95f37a71.d57b8469-d80d-4fed-b7bb-fd8b80e5b560.transition.description=There are more elements in the list. 379eeed2-0a73-4bb9-b26b-df9c95f37a71.description=
Tests a list of URLS to make sure they are responding.

Inputs\:
    List - The list of URLS that will be tested.
    seperator - A separator that is placed between each url that is in the list (must not be in any of the URLs themselves...).
    username - A username to use when connecting to the URLs.
    password - A password to use when connecting to the URLs.
    notifyMethod - How you would like to be notified of the test's outcome.
    timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
    socketTimeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for the data to be retrieved. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A socketTimeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
    useCookies - Enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. 
Default value\: true.
    followRedirects - Specifies whether or not the get command should automatically follow redirects.
Default value\: false.
    proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web site.
    proxyPort - The port on the proxy to connect to.
    proxyUsername - The username to use when connecting to the proxy.
    proxyPassword - The password to use when connecting to the proxy.
    encodeURL - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
    userAgent - The value that should be used if the HTTP header USER_AGENT has to be overridden.
    characterSet - The character encoding that should be used for the HTTP Get request and response. 
Default value\: UTF-8.
    trustAllRoots - Specifies whether to enable weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted certification authority issued it.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    keystore - The location of the KeyStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS client authentication is used. The default value will be provided if trustAllRoots is false.
Default\: /java/lib/security/cacerts
    keystorePassword - The password associated with the KeyStore file. If trustAllRoots is false and keystore is empty, keystorePassword default will be supplied.
Default value\: changeit
    trustKeystore - The location of the TrustStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS server authentication is used. The default value will be provided if trustAllRoots is false.
Default\: /java/lib/security/cacerts
    trustPassword - The password associated with the TrustStore file.  If trustAllRoots is false and trustKeystore is empty, trustPassword default will be supplied.
Default value\: changeit
    kerberosConfFile - Location of the kerberos conf file, used for ntlm authentication.
    headerNamesList - A list containing the names of headers that should be used for the request.
Example\: Accept,Content-Type
    headerValuesList - A list containing the values of headers that should be used for the request. 
Example\: text/plain,application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    queryNamesList - A list containing the names of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterName1,parameterName2 
    queryValuesList - A list containing the values of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterValue1,parameterValue2
    delimiter - A delimiter that separates the elements in the names and values lists.
Default value\: , (comma).

Responses\:
    success - All URLs passed the test, and the email was successfully sent.
    failure - Something went wrong.

Note\:
If you need to specify query parameters when making the request, consider using the “queryNamesList” and “queryValuesList” inputs. The operation also accepts including query parameters in the url (Example\: http\://hostname\:80/page.asp?parameterName1\=parameterValue1¶meterName2\=parameterValue2). If you specify the same query parameter both through the "queryNamesList" and through the url input, then the value from the "queryValuesList" list will be used and not the one included in the url.
379eeed2-0a73-4bb9-b26b-df9c95f37a71.dfe1b8db-f4ab-426f-a300-42e7d1519472.description=
Service to perform an HTTP GET via the Java HTTP Client.

Inputs\:
    url - The URL to attempt to retrieve.
    username - The username to use for authentication to the URL. For NTLM authentication, the required format is domain\user.
    password - The password to use for authentication to the URL.
    authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
    kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
    timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
    socketTimeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for the data to be retrieved. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A socketTimeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
    useCookies - If true, enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true.
    followRedirects - If true, the GET command automatically follows redirects. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
    proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web site.
    proxyPort - The port on the proxy to connect to.
    proxyUsername - The username to use when connecting to the proxy.
    proxyPassword - The password to use when connecting to the proxy.
    encodeURL - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
    userAgent - The value that should be used if the HTTP header USER_AGENT has to be overridden.
    characterSet - The character encoding that should be used for the HTTP Get request and response. 
Default value\: UTF-8.
    trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: false.
    keystore - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client  authentication is not to be used.
    keystorePassword - Password to unlock the keystore.
    trustKeystore - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
    trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore.
    headerNamesList - A list containing the names of headers that should be used for the request.
Example\: Accept,Content-Type
    headerValuesList - A list containing the values of headers that should be used for the request. 
Example\: text/plain,application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    queryNamesList - A list containing the names of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterName1,parameterName2 
    queryValuesList - A list containing the values of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterValue1,parameterValue2
    delimiter - A delimiter that separates the elements in the names and values lists.
Default value\: , (comma).

Results\:
    document - The complete document returned by the Http Client Get operation.
    pageLoadTimeInMS - The number of milliseconds it took the page to load.
    responseTimeInMS - The number of milliseconds it took before the server responded.
    urls - A list of URLs linked to by this page. Each URL is only listed once.
    URL - The url to GET from.
    sessionId - The session ID of the connection to the host.
    exception - If an error occurred, the stack trace of the thrown error.
    errorMessage - If an error occurred, an informational message that may help determine the cause of the error.
    resultText - The raw result of the operation.
    httpResult - A textual reason phrase describing the HTTP response that the web server returned for the request that this operation sent. This result contains the HTTP response status (e.g. SUCCESS, PAGE_NOT_FOUND, UNAUTHORIZED, FORBIDDEN, ...) or GENERAL_ERROR in case the HTTP request could not be executed by the operation.   
    status - The HTTP response code (e.g. HTTP/1.1 200 OK).
    responseHeaders - A list containing all the headers of the response message, separated by the delimiter.

Responses\:
    success - The URL retrieved successfully.
    failure - The URL could not be retrieved.

Notes\:
1. You can use keytool to import an ssl certificate in a keystore. For example to import a certificate in the Java cacerts keystore you should run\: keytool -import -file c\:/../.cer -alias  -keystore %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts -keystorepass changeit. If the keystore does not exist the command will try to create a new one containing only your certificate.
2. You can use keytool to create a certificate chain through the following command\: 
   keytool -genkey -dname "cn\=Mark Jones, ou\=JavaSoft, o\=Sun, c\=US" 
      -alias business -keypass kpi135 -keystore C\:\working\mykeystore 
      -storepass ab987c -validity 180
It creates a certificate chain in a new keystore containing only one certificate. This command is useful in case of ssl client authentication because the KeyManager ignores any certificates which are not included in a certificate chain.
3. If trustAllRoots \= false and trustKeystore is empty, the operation will try to use the default trust store with the password "changeit". (i.e.  %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts) 
4. If the authentication type is Kerberos you might need to add a SPN for the web server's computer account. In order to do this, you can use ADUC (Active Directory Users and Computers) with "Advanced Features" enabled. Just go to the web server's computer account (e.g. CN\=,CN\=Computers,DC\=domain,DC\=com), open the "Properties" window and hit the "Attribute Editor" tab. There should be an attribute named "servicePrincipalName". Observe the values of this attribute and add your SPN if not present (e.g. HTTP/\:port).
5. If you need to specify the request header fields, consider using the "headerNamesList" and "headerValuesList" inputs. The operation also accepts hidden inputs whose names begin with "header_", but this deprecated. You can add multiple headers.  For example, add an input name called "header_Content-Type" with a value as "text/html" and/or an input name called "header_Content-Length" with a value as "348".  The operation will strip off the "header_" prefix from the input name first, and the "Content-Type" and/or "Content-Length" header should be created with the value you specify. If you specify the same header both through the "headerNamesList" and through a "header_" hidden input, then the value from the "headerValuesList" list will be used and not the hidden input's value.
6. If you need to specify query parameters when making the request, consider using the “queryNamesList” and “queryValuesList” inputs. The operation also accepts including query parameters in the url (Example\: http\://hostname\:80/page.asp?parameterName1\=parameterValue1¶meterName2\=parameterValue2). If you specify the same query parameter both through the "queryNamesList" and through the url input, then the value from the "queryValuesList" list will be used and not the one included in the url.
7. Currently, the only supported application server when using form-based authentication is Apache Tomcat.

Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
